WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.240
Today, I'm going to be discussing a clinical trial evaluating iberdomyte versus lenandromyte

00:00:07.240 --> 00:00:12.760
in the post-transplant maintenance setting that Dr. Zander alluded to. Here are my disclosures.

00:00:14.240 --> 00:00:20.060
So just taking a step back, the goal of myeloma therapy for all transplant-eligible and

00:00:20.060 --> 00:00:26.400
ineligible patients is to try and capitalize on this initial opportunity to try and achieve the

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:32.560
best possible or deepest possible response, utilizing the most effective induction regimen

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:38.140
and trying to consolidate the response with transplant if feasible, and then offering

00:00:38.140 --> 00:00:44.540
very well-tolerated and effective maintenance strategies to try and prolong this PFS1 as much

00:00:44.540 --> 00:00:51.180
as possible. So recognizing that PFS1 is important and correlates to overall survival is important.

00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:56.180
So this figure kind of illustrates the depth of response,

00:00:56.400 --> 00:01:02.560
achieved at each level of therapy with induction, transplant, and then how maintenance therapy

00:01:02.560 --> 00:01:08.240
adds to delaying relapse in multiple myeloma, and this is so important as we try to

00:01:08.240 --> 00:01:14.480
find a cure for myeloma as a community. So just going back further in history as to how

00:01:14.480 --> 00:01:19.760
len maintenance became the center of care, so Dr. McCarthy's team kind of evaluated

00:01:20.400 --> 00:01:24.720
len maintenance versus observation in a large meta-analysis with 1,200 patients,

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:26.400
and what the study showed was that len maintenance and PFS1 are very similar.

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:31.760
The study showed was a dramatic improvement in PFS and OS in patients with len maintenance as

00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:38.560
compared to observation. The next question that was important was trying to determine if there's

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:45.120
fixed duration therapy or treatment under progression was better, and this question

00:01:45.120 --> 00:01:51.680
was tried to answer by the determination trial in the IFM 2009 study, and what we learned was that

00:01:51.680 --> 00:01:55.440
treatment under disease progression was associated with a better PFS as compared to observation.

00:01:55.440 --> 00:02:05.360
We also learned with different studies that len maintenance alone might not be adequate for the

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:11.520
high-risk or ultra-high-risk patients, so bottom line, len is the current center of care maintenance

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:18.080
regimen that is recommended. Continuing with maintenance therapy until disease progression

00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:24.320
is the way to go, especially for high-risk patients, and PFS and OS unfortunately still

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:29.280
remain inferior in the ultra-high-risk or high-risk patients with len maintenance alone as compared to

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:35.680
standard-risk patients. So that's why there are several combination agents that are being

00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:41.680
evaluated in the high-risk patients like I alluded to in my talk yesterday. But we all know we've all

00:02:41.680 --> 00:02:46.160
had patients that have been on len maintenance indefinitely, and the challenges that our patients

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:49.120
face in terms of the side-effect profile of len with diarrhea, cytopenias, fatigue, risk of thromboembolism, long-term risk of second primary care, and post-diagnostic treatment.

00:02:49.120 --> 00:03:04.960
And thus, there is a need to find maybe a better tolerated and more effective, if possible, maintenance agent for these patients.

00:03:06.560 --> 00:03:11.040
So here's a blurb about iberdomide. I think Dr. Zandra already covered this. It's a

00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:18.080
new cell mod agent, cerebron E3 ligase modulating agent that is shown to have superior potency

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:24.160
than len and may provide additional therapeutic benefit. So like Dr. Zandra alluded to, iberdomide

00:03:24.160 --> 00:03:29.280
binds to cerebron with a much higher binding affinity, causes deeper degradation of the

00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:34.720
icros and aloes, and has been shown to enhance myeloma cell killing and immune,

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:38.560
stronger immune activation of T cells and NK cells as compared to the imids.

00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:44.000
Unlike len, iber is actually administered as a single enantiomer in the S-isomer form,

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:49.120
which is maintained in vivo. And that might be the reason, or it can help to avoid certain

00:03:49.120 --> 00:03:52.640
side effects like sedation and fatigue that are attributed to the R-isomer.

00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:59.360
And based on the data coming out from the CC220 Phase 1, Phase 2 trial evaluating iber's safety

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:04.400
and efficacy in relapsed or factory patients, I think there is enough data justifying the use of

00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:08.320
this agent in earlier lines of treatment and especially in the maintenance setting.

00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:17.200
So this is a key trial, the EMN26, a Phase 2 multi-cohort study that is evaluating iberdomide

00:04:17.200 --> 00:04:22.080
at different dose levels in newly diagnosed myeloma patients that have achieved at least

00:04:22.080 --> 00:04:28.400
a PR with triplet or quadruplet induction therapy and can be enrolled for up to four months after

00:04:28.400 --> 00:04:33.520
transplant. The primary endpoint of the study was improvement in response within six months.

00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:39.040
And the second key secondary endpoints were rates of MRD conversion from positive to negative,

00:04:39.040 --> 00:04:45.120
PFS, and then the safety profile. Here's the baseline characteristics of the trial.

00:04:45.840 --> 00:04:50.960
What I would like to highlight is that in the 0.75 milligram cohort of iberdomide,

00:04:52.320 --> 00:04:58.000
higher frequency of patients received quadruplet induction with either data VTD or data

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:03.760
VRD as compared to the other dose cohorts. And they also received consolidation therapy more

00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:08.720
frequently than the other dose cohorts. So moving on to results, the trial didn't

00:05:08.720 --> 00:05:18.320
meet its primary endpoint of response improvement within six months. And we saw basically 36% all

00:05:18.320 --> 00:05:24.000
the way up to 59% response improvement within six months. And that's a null hypothesis of response

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:32.640
improvement of less than or equal to 20% was rejected. And in the 0.75 milligram cohort of

00:05:33.440 --> 00:05:38.720
iberdomide, 60% of the patients achieved MRD negative status at any time point. And the

00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:43.600
rates of conversion of MRD from positive to negative increased over time with this study.

00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:48.640
The two-year PFS in the 0.75 milligram cohort was 92%.

00:05:51.440 --> 00:05:56.960
In terms of adverse events, the major hematologic adverse event that was noted was neutropenia.

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:03.120
In grade three, grade four, neutropenia was seen in about 48% of the patients in the 0.75 milligram cohort.

00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:10.480
No grade three or four anemia or thrombocytopenia were reported. And in the 0.75 milligram cohort,

00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:17.200
apart from infections, very few other non-hematologic grade three, grade four adverse

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:24.080
events were noted. So it definitely has a more manageable safety profile. And thus based on these

00:06:24.080 --> 00:06:31.680
results, the 0.75 milligram dose of iberdomide was selected to be evaluated as a maintenance agent in

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:35.760
this last phase three multicenter randomized control trial, which is currently ongoing,

00:06:36.480 --> 00:06:43.360
evaluating head-to-head iberdomide maintenance against revlimid maintenance in newly diagnosed

00:06:43.360 --> 00:06:47.280
myeloma patients post-transplant. The primary endpoint was PFS and

00:06:47.280 --> 00:06:53.440
secondary endpoints of OS and MRD. The study is sort of ongoing and hoping to

00:06:54.400 --> 00:07:00.720
we get some more updates about this study in this upcoming ASHRAE meeting. And thus I would like to

00:07:00.720 --> 00:07:07.360
conclude that iberdomide maintenance led to response improvement over time in patients with

00:07:07.360 --> 00:07:12.000
newly diagnosed myeloma post-induction and transplant, and it compared favorably with

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:19.440
len maintenance. Iber actually demonstrated 46 to 72% response improvement at cycle 12 as compared

00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:27.520
to 31% that was noted with len maintenance in the prior EMN2 study. Promising rates of MRD conversion

00:07:27.520 --> 00:07:33.360
were reported with iberdomide maintenance and iber showed a manageable safety profile with very few

00:07:33.360 --> 00:07:39.440
grade three grade four non-hematologic adverse events that were reported. And the 0.75 milligram

00:07:39.440 --> 00:07:44.480
dose of iberdomide is now being compared head to head with revlimid in the large phase three

00:07:44.480 --> 00:07:49.280
Excalibur maintenance trial. Hopefully we get a readout soon at this ASH. With that,

00:07:49.280 --> 00:07:53.360
I would like to thank my Emory Myeloma Group and happy to take questions.
